race.comment: ADMIRE ASTRA (7) went through to the Champion Fillies before going for a break. Her trial this time in was solid and 1400m on the fresh side looks a good move. Needs some luck from out wide but can storm home over the top. TORA BORA (11) won well two back before a sound effort in tougher company last start at this track and trip. That was a hot 3YO race and Nottle's claim comes in handy as she'll carry no weight. Can put her best foot forward. SOLDIER OF GOD (2) disappointed last start when pulling up with an issue but was in good form prior. Can bounce back. AITCH MONTANA (8) was too strong from the front last start and can turn in a bold performance once again.
